**Once upon a time, there was a group of little sheep that lived in a beautiful green pasture. They were fluffy and white, with big curious eyes. Each one had its own personality, some were shy, while others were playful. Every day, the sheep followed the shepherd, a tall and strong man, as he led them to graze in different parts of the pasture. The sheep loved following the shepherd, knowing that he would protect and care for them. One day, a little sheep named Dolly wandered away from the group and got lost. She felt scared and alone, but suddenly saw a big dog coming towards her. The sheep was afraid, but the dog started licking her face and cuddling her. Dolly realized that the dog just wanted to play and have fun with her. Finally, the shepherd found Dolly and the dog playing together and brought the sheep back to the group. From then on, all the sheep became friends with the dog and played with him whenever he came to the pasture.** - Upscaled by <@737111057788698725> (fast)
